e-apps/file-schema/runtime/qualifyassembly-element.md) element in the application configuration file."},{"content":"This element allows you to provide the full reference information (name, version, culture and, if applicable, the public key token) in your application configuration file instead of in your code.","pos":[3566,3761]},{"content":"You would use this technique if you wanted to fully qualify a reference to an assembly outside the application directory, or if you wanted to reference an assembly in the global assembly cache but you wanted the convenience of specifying the full reference in the configuration file instead of in your code.","pos":[3762,4069]},{"pos":[4077,4452],"content":"[!NOTE]\n This type of partial reference should not be used with assemblies that are shared among several applications. Because configuration settings are applied per application and not per assembly, a shared assembly using this type of partial reference would require each application using the shared assembly to have the qualifying information in its configuration file.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"This type of partial reference should not be used with assemblies that are shared among several applications. Because configuration settings are applied per application and not per assembly, a shared assembly using this type of partial reference would require each application using the shared assembly to have the qualifying information in its configuration file.","pos":[9,373],"nodes":[{"content":"This type of partial reference should not be used with assemblies that are shared among several applications.","pos":[0,109]},{"content":"Because configuration settings are applied per application and not per assembly, a shared assembly using this type of partial reference would require each application using the shared assembly to have the qualifying information in its configuration file.","pos":[110,364]}]}]},{"content":"The runtime uses the following steps to resolve an assembly reference:","pos":[4459,4529]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Determines the correct assembly version<ept id=\"p1\">](#step1)</ept> by examining applicable configuration files, including the application configuration file, publisher policy file, and machine configuration file.","pos":[4539,4734],"source":"[Determines the correct assembly version](#step1) by examining applicable configuration files, including the application configuration file, publisher policy file, and machine configuration file."},{"content":"If the configuration file is located on a remote machine, the runtime must locate and download the application configuration file first.","pos":[4735,4871]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Checks whether the assembly name has been bound to before<ept id=\"p1\">](#step2)</ept> and, if so, uses the previously loaded assembly.","pos":[4881,4997],"source":"[Checks whether the assembly name has been bound to before](#step2) and, if so, uses the previously loaded assembly."},{"content":"If a previous request to load the assembly failed, the request is failed immediately without attempting to load the assembly.","pos":[4998,5123]},{"pos":[5135,5232],"content":"[!NOTE]\nThe caching of assembly binding failures is new in the .NET Framework version 2.0.","leadings":["","    >  "],"nodes":[{"content":"The caching of assembly binding failures is new in the .NET Framework version 2.0.","pos":[8,90]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Checks the global assembly cache<ept id=\"p1\">](#step3)</ept>.","pos":[5242,5285],"source":"[Checks the global assembly cache](#step3)."},{"content":"If the assembly is found there, the runtime uses this assembly.","pos":[5286,5349]},{"pos":[5359,5419],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Probes for the assembly<ept id=\"p1\">](#step4)</ept> using the following steps:","source":"[Probes for the assembly](#step4) using the following steps:"},{"content":"If configuration and publisher policy do not affect the original reference and if the bind request was created using the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Reflection.Assembly.LoadFrom%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> method, the runtime checks for location hints.","pos":[5433,5671],"source":"If configuration and publisher policy do not affect the original reference and if the bind request was created using the <xref:System.Reflection.Assembly.LoadFrom%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method, the runtime checks for location hints."},{"content":"If a codebase is found in the configuration files, the runtime checks only this location.","pos":[5685,5774]},{"content":"If this probe fails, the runtime determines that the binding request failed and no other probing occurs.","pos":[5775,5879]},{"content":"Probes for the assembly using the heuristics described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>probing section<ept id=\"p1\">](#step4)</ept>.","pos":[5893,5981],"source":"Probes for the assembly using the heuristics described in the [probing section](#step4)."},{"content":"If the assembly is not found after probing, the runtime requests the Windows Installer to provide the assembly.","pos":[5982,6093]},{"content":"This acts as an install-on-demand feature.","pos":[6094,6136]},{"pos":[6152,6329],"content":"[!NOTE]\nThere is no version checking for assemblies without strong names, nor does the runtime check in the global assembly cache for assemblies without strong names.","leadings":["","        >  "],"nodes":[{"content":"There is no version checking for assemblies without strong names, nor does the runtime check in the global assembly cache for assemblies without strong names.","pos":[8,166]}]},{"pos":[6362,6403],"content":"Step 1: Examining the Configuration Files","linkify":"Step 1: Examining the Configuration Files","nodes":[{"content":"Step 1: Examining the Configuration Files","pos":[0,41]}]},{"content":"Assembly binding behavior can be configured at different levels based on three XML files:","pos":[6407,6496]},{"content":"Application configuration file.","po