nd private path information can only be in the application configuration file.","pos":[128,233]},{"content":"For a complete list of the information that is contained in each file, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configuring Apps by Using Configuration Files<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)</ept>.","pos":[234,406],"source":" For a complete list of the information that is contained in each file, see [Configuring Apps by Using Configuration Files](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)."}]}]},{"pos":[8173,8203],"content":"Application Configuration File","linkify":"Application Configuration File","nodes":[{"content":"Application Configuration File","pos":[0,30]}]},{"content":"First, the common language runtime checks the application configuration file for information that overrides the version information stored in the calling assembly's manifest.","pos":[8207,8381]},{"content":"The application configuration file can be deployed with an application, but is not required for application execution.","pos":[8382,8500]},{"content":"Usually the retrieval of this file is almost instantaneous, but in situations where the application base is on a remote computer, such as in an Internet Explorer Web-based scenario, the configuration file must be downloaded.","pos":[8501,8725]},{"content":"For client executables, the application configuration file resides in the same directory as the application's executable and has the same base name as the executable with a .config extension.","pos":[8732,8923]},{"content":"For example, the configuration file for C:\\Program Files\\Myapp\\Myapp.exe is C:\\Program Files\\Myapp\\Myapp.exe.config. In a browser-based scenario, the HTML file must use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>link&gt;<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> element to explicitly point to the configuration file.","pos":[8924,9163],"source":" For example, the configuration file for C:\\Program Files\\Myapp\\Myapp.exe is C:\\Program Files\\M