tion, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configuring Apps by using Configuration Files<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)</ept>.","pos":[13406,13537],"source":" For more about configuration, see [Configuring Apps by using Configuration Files](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)."},{"pos":[13547,13573],"content":"Machine Configuration File","linkify":"Machine Configuration File","nodes":[{"content":"Machine Configuration File","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"Third, the runtime examines the machine configuration file.","pos":[13577,13636]},{"content":"This file, called Machine.config, resides on the local computer in the Config subdirectory of the root directory where the runtime is installed.","pos":[13637,13781]},{"content":"This file can be used by administrators to specify assembly binding restrictions that are local to that computer.","pos":[13782,13895]},{"content":"The settings in the machine configuration file take precedence over all other configuration settings; however, this does not mean that all configuration settings should be put in this file.","pos":[13896,14085]},{"content":"The version determined by the administrator policy file is final, and cannot be overridden.","pos":[14086,14177]},{"content":"Overrides specified in the Machine.config file affect all applications.","pos":[14178,14249]},{"content":"For more information about configuration files, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configuring Apps by using Configuration Files<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)</ept>.","pos":[14250,14399],"source":" For more information about configuration files, see [Configuring Apps by using Configuration Files](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/index.md)."},{"pos":[14432,14485],"content":"Step 2: Checking for Previously Referenced Assemblies","linkify":"Step 2: Checking for Previously Referenced Assemblies","nodes":[{"content":"Step 2: Checking for Previously Referenced Assemblies","pos":[0,53]}]},{"content"